  "text": "It is also notable that this readability level is too high for patients and their families. The average reading level in the United States is estimated to be around 8th grade [CITATION_1] . Foe and Larson (2016) rec ommend a reading level of health information materials to be between the 6th and 8th grade levels. This means the aver age report from any laboratory is substantially beyond most patient's or family's reading comprehension. Unfortunately, genetic information is often important not only to the patient but also to the extended family. Providing a family section may help not only the patient and provider, but also extended at-risk family members.",
